  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Currently testnet & mainnet can be selected using envVars via `IS_MAINNET`. The complexity of different nets is not entirely captured by this model. and so it should be extended to support multiple configurations. Each net can vary in the following parameters:\r\n* is_tesnet\r\n* network name\r\n* deposit amount\r\n* deposit contract address\r\n* fork version\r\n* eth1 network (Goerlli vs mainnet etc)\r\n\r\nThese options are all properties of the network and should be swapped out depending on which one is active. As discussed in #83, all these parameters can be populated as envVars which possibly default to the mainnet configuration. ",
