    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "We started to look into the implementation, and it would be helpful if you could expand on this comment.\r\n> Testnet/mainnet swapping once deployed: I think we can lock it down and if someone want to change, they can be redirected (like block explorers do if you switch networks)\r\n\r\nDoes this mean that we will have different Launchpad deployments for each eth2 network? For instance, do we want `witti.launchpad.ethereum.org` to be a deployment with a witti config similar to block explorers like`goerli.etherscan.io`? If so, this would be a much lighter of a lift as we could just have a configuration per deployment. For this case, we could have links or a dropdown that would navigate users to the appropriate deployment URL. \r\n\r\nOr\r\n\r\nDo we want one testnet deployment with a dynamic config that is changed by a dropdown? This would mean that the user toggles the eth2 network on the Overview page and it switches the config in application state, allowing the user to access all eth2 testnets on this single deployment. We could also put in place a Mainnet environment variable which will override the testnet configs and not render the dropdown on the Overview page.\r\n\r\nEither would work, we just need clarification on which as it drastically changes the UX and DevOps.",
